\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.1}{\ignorespaces The Vol 11 complete harmonic portrait. Every confirmed STRONG domain is plotted at its best register on the $N/\pi $ axis. The B5 full backbone (large green triangle, upper right, $25/\pi $, $Z=+157$) is the defining new result of this volume. The B4 Top8000 backbone (darker green triangle, $19/\pi $, $Z=+121$) replicates the Vol 10 kinematic biology result. The two green triangles at different x-positions with different y-heights are the resolution sensitivity discovery made visible. Stellar colour (gold star, $20/\pi $, $Z=+124$) is the first confirmed electromagnetic property lock. Tidal suite (blue triangles at $17/\pi $--$18/\pi $--$24/\pi $) confirms four ocean basins. Subnuclear dual-peak (gold pentagons at $13/\pi $ and $22/\pi $) motivates the Vol 12 two-dimensional engine. Anti-signals (grey crosses below zero) are positional and mass quantities that the kinematic principle predicts will not lock. The kinematic ceiling at $24/\pi $ holds: no kinematic domain breached it.}}{17}{figure.3.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:v11_portrait}{{3.1}{17}{The Vol 11 complete harmonic portrait. Every confirmed STRONG domain is plotted at its best register on the $N/\pi $ axis. The B5 full backbone (large green triangle, upper right, $25/\pi $, $Z=+157$) is the defining new result of this volume. The B4 Top8000 backbone (darker green triangle, $19/\pi $, $Z=+121$) replicates the Vol 10 kinematic biology result. The two green triangles at different x-positions with different y-heights are the resolution sensitivity discovery made visible. Stellar colour (gold star, $20/\pi $, $Z=+124$) is the first confirmed electromagnetic property lock. Tidal suite (blue triangles at $17/\pi $--$18/\pi $--$24/\pi $) confirms four ocean basins. Subnuclear dual-peak (gold pentagons at $13/\pi $ and $22/\pi $) motivates the Vol 12 two-dimensional engine. Anti-signals (grey crosses below zero) are positional and mass quantities that the kinematic principle predicts will not lock. The kinematic ceiling at $24/\pi $ holds: no kinematic domain breached it}{figure.3.1}{}}
