\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {3.3}{\ignorespaces The three null distributions generated per domain. Each null is independently archived as a sovereign JSONL file in the pipeline's synthetic lakes directory. The chaos stage output for each domain reports the real fraction, the chaos fraction, and the synthetic fraction at each register. The delta ($\Delta = \text  {real} - \text  {chaos}$) is the primary signal statistic. A result is STRONG only when the real data exceeds the chaos null at $Z \geq 5$ at some register, and the synthetic z-score is consistent with the interpretation.}}{18}{table.3.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:three_nulls}{{3.3}{18}{The three null distributions generated per domain. Each null is independently archived as a sovereign JSONL file in the pipeline's synthetic lakes directory. The chaos stage output for each domain reports the real fraction, the chaos fraction, and the synthetic fraction at each register. The delta ($\Delta = \text {real} - \text {chaos}$) is the primary signal statistic. A result is STRONG only when the real data exceeds the chaos null at $Z \geq 5$ at some register, and the synthetic z-score is consistent with the interpretation}{table.3.3}{}}
